725644f-a.title: Queens: 76th Avenue - Parsons Boulevard
725644f-a.text:
76th Avenue, adjoining the N.E. corner of Parsons Boule-
vard, showing two of a large group of new homes, erected here
by the Stewart Homes builders.
MAY BE REPRODUCED  About 1927

727672f-a.title: Queens: Parsons Boulevard - 76th Avenue
727672f-a.text:
Tarsons Boulevard, west side, north from 77th Avenue to
76th Road, showing old homes on the former Jamaica Road.
The first house, evidently of 18th century construction, was
the property of either Mrs. Acker or the Monitor Peat Company
in 187S. It was later (1891) owned by J. Keisel and was a
hotel in 1909, the owner of which was Henry Kessel.
P. L. Sperr  March 23, 1927
NO REPRODUCTIONS
